    https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_p_v2.txt

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Why two licenses?
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Hardware and software have different reuse and liability concerns. CERN-OHL-P is
purpose-built for hardware sources and clearly defines terms like "Product" and
"Source"; MIT is the most frictionless choice for the model and tooling, so
anyone can drop the engine into their own stack without ceremony.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Not financial advice
----------------------------------------------------------------------
This is a hardware research project. It computes moving averages, it does not
make trading decisions and it makes no promises about money. Trading is risky.
Use it at your own risk, and read the warranty disclaimer above twice.
